I know that we can fit a gam model like this: 

gam(y ~ f + s(x, by = f), data = d)

But now assume the factor f has only 2 levels and we fit the model like: 

gam(y ~ s(x, by = f) + s(f, bs = "re"), data = d).

Does this make sense? When and why? #rstats
